The paper deals with algorithms for preconditioning and solving linear systems, which are typically studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of subgraph preconditioners and the application to Fiedler vectors suggest that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the hope for practical fast algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SI).
